  "prompt": "If I connect USB OTG pendrive to my power bank and connect the other point with data cable to my mobile, will pendrive be working on my mobile?",
  "response": "No, connecting a USB OTG (On-The-Go) pendrive to a power bank and then connecting the power bank to your mobile phone via a data cable **will not** allow the pendrive to work on your mobile.\n\nHere\u2019s why:\n\n1. **Power Bank's Role**: A power bank is designed to supply power to other devices (like your phone) and does not support data transfer or OTG functionality. It acts as a power source, not a data hub.\n\n2. **OTG Functionality**: USB OTG is a feature that allows your mobile phone to act as a host for USB devices like pendrives, keyboards, or mice. However, for this to work, the OTG device (pendrive) must be directly connected to the phone using an OTG cable or adapter.\n\n3. **Data Cable Connection**: The data cable from the power bank to your phone only transfers power, not data. The pendrive is not part of the data communication path in this setup.\n\n### How to Make It Work:\nTo use a USB OTG pendrive with your mobile:\n- Use a **USB OTG adapter** or cable to connect the pendrive directly to your phone.\n- Ensure your phone supports USB OTG functionality (most modern Android phones do).\n- Your phone will then recognize the pendrive and allow you to access its files.\n\nLet me know if you have further questions!",
